                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Back to the question at hand....
<br />

<br />
Why the hype....
<br />

<br />
Why are people looking forward to this game...
<br />

<br />
I will open by saying, clearly, whether you are negative about the game or not, you all, at some point, have invested a huge amount of time into EQ.  Why?
<br />

<br />
Those of us that remember the early days, remember how amazing and awe inspiring EQ was.  I don't know that any game will ever match that, ever.
<br />

<br />
That being said, I think the reason people are looking forward to Vanguard can be summed up with one word - faith.
<br />

<br />
Faith in the development team that has been assembled.  Faith that the people making the game are more interested in creating a huge immersive world and not bending to the whiners, which, I believe, ruined EQ.
<br />

<br />
Faith in the Art Director, Keith Parkinson.  Faith in Brad McQuaid and Jeff Butler in their ability to deliver something that will immerse and spark our imaginations.  
<br />

<br />
Faith that these guys not only can and have delivered an amazing game, but will deliver again.  
<br />

<br />
Faith that these people understand that the communities that spring up around a game are important.  Proof of that is the that their boards are already hopping and the game isn't any where near release.
<br />

<br />
I for one, hope we see a return to the days where we all knew our GM who lived on our server.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ungzaba Bruja, 70 Wizard, Vazaelle
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=724977" target="_blank" class="postlink">My Ghetto Gear</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
