                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Any and all game makers have been more than loquacious on message boards during their developement.  However, when the shit goes live things change radically.  The customers are no longer "fans" with their messages of support and awe, they are now "users" with their messages of hate, annoyance, and whinning.  I don't care if Brad McFugginQuad is running around giving hand jobs, it doesn't speak to what their communication levels will be like when the product is live.
<br />

<br />
Talk to some old school EQ1 beta testers.  Ask them how communicative Brad and co were then?  How communicative is SoE now?  Hell, how communicative was Brad one year after release?
<br />

<br />
It doesn't mean jack.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />/rude</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
