                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Not only does a member of Microsofts staff pipe in, the man himself, Brad McQuaid stops in to lend some helpful information. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Brad has been very approachable actually. All of them have been.
<br />

<br />
The thing is... I was in IRC and "The Vision" stepped into the room. I point blank asked if Vanguard will be hard, or whether it will baby people along.
<br />
Answer?
<br />
It'll be hard. You'll feel like you've achieved something. We won't dumb it down. Death will hurt. There will be corpse runs. There will be *difficult* corpse runs. You will have to WALK places. 
<br />

<br />
I thanked him for the answer and sat back.
<br />
I sat staring at the screen thinking 'EQ, all over again, before Graveyards (I love graveyards lol), with boats and long runs with peril at every turn. Stuff that will leave you shaking in front of your PC because it's SCARY.'
<br />
My next thought was 'I am SO in.'
<br />

<br />
Thing is... I don't want a dumbed down game that anyone can beat.
<br />
I don't want a game which has no real challenges.
<br />
I don't want my quests spoonfed to me by way of telling me exactly what to do.
<br />

<br />
EQ to me is (well ok, was) 2 parts challenge, 2 parts discovery, 1 part huge chatroom, with a sprinkle of "Wow!" in places, and a dash of '"Oh shit!" to keep the heart pumping.
<br />

<br />
EQ2 is not for me. I knew that in Beta so luckily it saved me from buying the game to see what it's like.
<br />

<br />
I want the above recipe back.
<br />
Vanguard sounds like it'll do just that.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
