                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">That said, I wonder if there are any fresh ideas left in the fantasy genre anymore?
<br />

<br />
How much longer will the same ol, Dwarf, halfling, gnome, human, OMGZ can't forget the Dark Elves (Drow)  <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" />  keep people's attention.
<br />

<br />
The genre is very tired.  I'd like to see a nice post apocalyptic MMOG go live with Psionics, Magic and technology jockying for power, ala Rifts - and don't say AO!
<br />

<br />

<br />
Hmmm....
<br />

<br />
Looks like the Rifts World already has enough content to support years of expantions - just need a publisher and design team.  I wonder why they haven't tried to break into the MMOG Genre yet.
<br />

<br />
The Source Books outlining the mechanics.
<br />
<a href="http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=R800" target="_blank">http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=R800</a>
<br />

<br />
Conversion Mechanics for porting characters from other games in
<br />
<a href="http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=C800" target="_blank">http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=C800</a>
<br />

<br />
Content Expantions
<br />
<a href="http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=D800" target="_blank">http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=D800</a>
<br />

<br />
World Books Detailing NPCs and Regional Culture and Characteristics
<br />
<a href="http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=W800" target="_blank">http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=W800</a>
<br />

<br />
Rifts Miniatures - 3 dimentional concept art!
<br />
<a href="http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=M8000" target="_blank">http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=M8000</a>
<br />

<br />
aside from all that, the rifts word and game mechanics are interchangable with the regular Palladium Fantasty World.
<br />
<a href="http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=F450" target="_blank">http://store.palladiumbooks.com/Merchant2/merchant.mv?Screen=CTGY&Category_Code=F450</a>
<br />

<br />
Rifts Story line would allow for travel between universes and dimentions.  It is completely wide open.  Add to that the Robotec mechanics and content.
<br />

<br />
Again I wonder why no one has pitched this - there is an endless amount of content and world already developed aside from a wide open system for skill based character development (the most fun aspect of this game), Unique and interesting classes from Juicers (humans literally cracked out), to Borgs, Psionicists, Warlocks....</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ungzaba Bruja, 70 Wizard, Vazaelle
