                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been thinking for years how the Feist's creation would be a great setting for a fantasy MMORPG. Start out as some race in Midkemia. If non-human but good, they can be explained as studen'ts in Pug's academy. If evil they can start out in that other continent (forget it's name but the one the emerald queen came from). Probably an experimental magic gone awry by the Pantathians. Good would obviously be working for Pug and his order and if you're evil, Nalar is the head honcho. Expansions would be easily handled as you would enter the Hall to access new content but only if you are of sufficient level/abilites. They would also have unlimited freedom in creating either technological worlds or more traditional fantasy worlds or both as this is covered and mentioned (though only briefly) in Feist's novels. 
<br />

<br />
Am I the only one that thought the Conclave of Shadows trilogy was weak? I was hoping for more on the agents of Nalar against the Conclave itself. If anyone remembers from I believe Rage of a Demon King, Pug is suppose to be paying a huge price for his ressurection. I thought they would be delving into that or maybe Feist is planning on doing that in the next series. While I don't think the last trilogy was bad, it just wasn't what I was expecting. The agents of Nalar was only very very briefly mentioned. All that buildup from the Serpentwar Saga about Nalar and such and then CoS had almost zip on it.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">On the other hand, if your reaction to something I say boils down to "You didn't choose MY side, make MY choice," well, you're not looking for information, you're looking for someone to tell you how smart you are thinking the way you do. --</span> <span style="font-weight: bold">Ed Stroligo</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
